# Security Implementation Overview

## Content Security Policy (CSP)
The CSP implementation is defined in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/server/middleware.ts) and includes:
- Strict resource loading rules for scripts, styles, images, and fonts
- Trusted domains for analytics and content delivery
- Protection against XSS and other injection attacks

## Rate Limiting
Rate limiting rules are defined in [rateLimiter.ts](mdc:src/server/rateLimiter.ts) with different limits for:
- General API: 100 requests/15 minutes
- Authentication: 5 requests/hour
- Forms: 10 requests/hour
- Contentful: 30 requests/minute
- Health checks: 60 requests/minute

## Security Headers
Additional security headers are implemented in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/server/middleware.ts):
- X-Content-Type-Options
- X-Frame-Options
- X-XSS-Protection
- Referrer-Policy
- Permissions-Policy
- Strict-Transport-Security

## Testing
Security tests are located in [rateLimiter.test.ts](mdc:src/server/__tests__/rateLimiter.test.ts) and verify:
- Rate limiting functionality
- Request blocking at limits
- Header presence and values

## Integration
The security middleware is integrated into the Vite development server in [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts).
